<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 02 at 3:54PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A thunderstorm will impact portions of southern Gallatin County
through 430 PM MDT...
At 353 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a thunderstorm 7 miles
northwest of Crescent Lake, or 23 miles northwest of Mammoth, moving
east at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph, brief heavy rain, and occasional
lightning strikes.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of southern Gallatin
County.
This includes Highway 191 between mile markers 31 and 42.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
